column5: Just wondering what the ice conditions are of Lake Simcoe? I have never ice fished Simcoe before, but was thinking about going next weekend.  Also, some helpful tips on where to go would be appreciated. I am looking for walleye/perch/crappie.  Thanks in advance.
Hmmm, what Clamp-it said.  Walleye, mostly found around Talbot area in the spring, Crappie, they go south for the winter and show up when the ice melts in little marinas and harbours.
pretty sure you can catch a perch anywhere you drop a line in that lake
